narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Practiced presenting on independent research and listened to others' presentations.

This course was a wonderful introduction to the real life of chemistry. Dr. Parr did a great job in teaching how working in a lab postgrad will be like, as well as setting us up with the appropriate steps to take in order to have a successful career in the chemistry field.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: supports independent research in the chemistry department, provides presentation practice Weaknesses: high variability based on PI, research project; 490 seminar is not very structured
Major strength of this class is how relaxed it is. It made me feel very comfortable asking questions and learning along side the undergrads I spent my four years of chemistry with.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Have to take if performing independent research for the CHEM senior requirement. It is a good way to practice speaking and presenting your work.
